I'm a fan of this Cafe which serves up breakfast, dessert, and lunch dishes with an emphasis on Brazilian influenced. Breakfast you'll find standard options like fried eggs, pancakes, & French toast, with some chef specials like their House Huevos Rancheros and fantastic Breakfast Burrito. For Lunch you'll find paninis, classic sandwiches, salads, subs, burrito (tortilla or bowl), pastas, and a special Brazilian menu of entrees (Grilled Chicken, Steak, Tilapia, Pork Sirloin) and sandwiches (give the Brazilian Style Burger a try! Includes egg, ham, grilled chicken, peas, corn, and potato sticks). Good beverage selection such as cappuccino, expresso, chai lattes, gourmet hot chocolate, and tea. Lots of coffee drinks here.  Prices are quite reasonable and portions are substantial. They do a good job with providing optional add-ons for certain dishes, giving the customer some flexibility. The place is clean / modern (tables / seating reflect our covid times).

I stopped by this cafe on the edge of Assembly sq mall looking for a coffee and perhaps a sandwich, but noticed that they had a bunch of Brazilian cuisine options on the menu, and decided to try the steak dinner since I love Brazilian food and everyone who worked at the cafe seemed Brazilian. I normally would temper my expectations when ordering a full meal at a place like this, given that it isn't their specialty, and I figured that into my rating. Needless to say, the meal was disappointing; the rice was mushy and bland, steak was tough and ringed by a layer of fat, and beans tasted like they were out of a can. If I were the owner, I'd rework this range of items, or drop them altogether. On the plus side, service was friendly.
